properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued January 31 at 2:08AM PST until February 1 at 7:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...South winds 25 to 45 mph with gusts up to 50-60 mph
expected.

* WHERE...San Juan County, Western Whatcom County, Western
Skagit County, Everett and Vicinity, Admiralty Inlet Area,
North Coast and Central Coast.

* WHEN...From 10 AM this morning to 7 AM PST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Damaging winds will blow down trees and power lines.
Widespread power outages are expected. Travel will be
difficult, especially for high profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The strongest winds are expected to be late
this afternoon through this evening.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use caution if
you must drive.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM THIS MORNING TO 7 AM PST SATURDAY
